<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Members confirm their commitment to give preference to those measures which have the least disruptive effect on trade. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmed kinnitavad oma kohustust eelistada neid meetmeid, mis h&auml;irivad kaubandust k&otilde;ige v&auml;hem. </eesti>
<inglise> Such measures (referred to in this Understanding as "price-based measures") shall be understood to include import surcharges, import deposit requirements or other equivalent trade measures with an impact on the price of imported goods. </inglise>
<eesti> Selliseid meetmeid (k&auml;esolevas k&auml;situsleppes "hinnap&otilde;hised meetmed") k&auml;sitatakse nii, et nad h&otilde;lmavad lisamakseid impordilt, sissemaksen&otilde;udeid impordilt ja muid samav&auml;&auml;rseid kaubandusmeetmeid, mis avaldavad m&otilde;ju importkaupade hinnale. </eesti>
<inglise> It is understood that, notwithstanding the provisions of Article II, price-based measures taken for balance-of-payments purposes may be applied by a Member in excess of the duties inscribed in the Schedule of that Member. </inglise>
<eesti> Ollakse seisukohal, et hoolimata II artikli s&auml;tetest v&otilde;ib liige rakendada seoses maksebilansiga v&otilde;etud hinnap&otilde;hiseid meetmeid lisaks selle liikme loendisse m&auml;rgitud tollimaksudele. </eesti>
<inglise> Furthermore, that Member shall indicate the amount by which the price-based measure exceeds the bound duty clearly and separately under the notification procedures of this Understanding. </inglise>
<eesti> Veel enam, k&auml;esolevas k&auml;situsleppes s&auml;testatud teatamisprotseduuride alusel n&auml;itab see liige selgelt ja eraldi summa, mille v&otilde;rra k&otilde;nesolev hinnap&otilde;hine meede &uuml;letab seotud tollimaksu. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> Members shall seek to avoid the imposition of new quantitative restrictions for balance-of-payments purposes unless, because of a critical balance-of-payments situation, price-based measures cannot arrest a sharp deterioration in the external payments position. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmed p&uuml;&uuml;avad v&auml;ltida uute kvantitatiivsete piirangute kehtestamist seoses maksebilansiga, v&auml;lja arvatud juhul, kui hinnap&otilde;histe meetmete abil ei saa maksebilansi kriitilise olukorra t&otilde;ttu peatada v&auml;lismaksepositsiooni j&auml;rsku halvenemist. </eesti>
<inglise> In those cases in which a Member applies quantitative restrictions, it shall provide justification as to the reasons why price-based measures are not an adequate instrument to deal with the balance-of-payments situation. </inglise>
