<inglise> 4. </inglise>
<eesti> 4. </eesti>
<inglise> Members confirm that restrictive import measures taken for balance-of-payments purposes may only be applied to control the general level of imports and may not exceed what is necessary to address the balance-of-payments situation. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmed kinnitavad, et seoses maksebilansiga v&otilde;etud piiravaid impordimeetmeid v&otilde;idakse rakendada &uuml;ksnes kontrollimaks impordi &uuml;ldtaset ja need ei tohi &uuml;letada maksebilansi olukorra parandamiseks vajalikke. </eesti>
<inglise> In order to minimize any incidental protective effects, a Member shall administer restrictions in a transparent manner. </inglise>
<eesti> Juhusliku protektsionistliku m&otilde;ju miinimumini v&auml;hendamiseks haldab liige piiranguid selgelt. </eesti>
<inglise> The authorities of the importing Member shall provide adequate justification as to the criteria used to determine which products are subject to restriction. </inglise>
<eesti> Importijaliikme v&otilde;imuorganid esitavad asjakohase p&otilde;hjenduse kriteeriumide kohta, mida kasutatakse m&auml;&auml;ramaks, milliste toodete suhtes piirangud kehtivad. </eesti>
<inglise> As provided in paragraph 3 of Article XII and paragraph 10 of Article XVIII, Members may, in the case of certain essential products, exclude or limit the application of surcharges applied across the board or other measures applied for balance-of-payments purposes. </inglise>
<eesti> Vastavalt XII artikli l&otilde;ikes 3 ja XVIII artikli l&otilde;ikes 10 s&auml;testatule v&otilde;ivad liikmed teatavate esmat&auml;htsate toodete puhul &auml;ra j&auml;tta v&otilde;i piirata k&otilde;ikeh&otilde;lmavalt rakendatud lisamakseid v&otilde;i muid seoses maksebilansiga rakendatud meetmeid. </eesti>
